    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Chop your <strong>potatoes </strong>into small bite-sized pieces</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped potatoes </strong>to a large heat-proof bowl covered with<strong> cling film</strong></p><p>Put the bowl in the <strong>microwave</strong> for 6-8 min or until slightly tender</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/crab-aguachile-style-toasts-with-quick-pickled-chilli-potatoes/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, slice <strong>half</strong> your <strong>green chilli[es]</strong> into rounds and finely dice the <strong>remaining chilli[es]</strong></p><p>Peel and slice your <strong>shallot[s]</strong> finely</p><p>Roll your <strong>lime[s]</strong> with your hand on a hard surface (to release more juice) and cut into wedges</p><p>Combine the juice of <strong>half</strong> the <strong>lime</strong> and 1 tsp [1 1/2 tsp] [2 tsp] <strong>sugar</strong> with the <strong>chilli rounds</strong> and <strong>sliced shallot</strong> \u2013 this is your <strong>quick-pickled chilli</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/crab-aguachile-style-toasts-with-quick-pickled-chilli-potatoes/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the potatoes are slightly tender, transfer them to a <strong>baking paper</strong>-lined baking tray with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>and a pinch of<strong> salt</strong></p><p>Put the tray in the oven for an initial 10 min</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/crab-aguachile-style-toasts-with-quick-pickled-chilli-potatoes/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Cut your <strong>cucumber</strong> into thin batons, then dice finely</p><p>Chop your <strong>tomato[es]</strong> finely</p><p>Chop your <strong>coriander </strong>roughly, including the stalks (save some leaves for a garnish!)</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/crab-aguachile-style-toasts-with-quick-pickled-chilli-potatoes/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Combine your <strong>crab meat</strong> with the <strong>diced cucumber</strong>, <strong>chopped tomato</strong> and <strong>chopped coriander</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>diced chilli </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!), and a generous squeeze of <strong>lime juice</strong></p><p>Add your <strong>mayo</strong> with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper </strong>and give everything a good mix up \u2013 this is your <strong>crab aguachile</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/crab-aguachile-style-toasts-with-quick-pickled-chilli-potatoes/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Slice your <strong>ciabatta[s]</strong> in half</p><p>Once the potatoes have had an initial 10 min, add the <strong>sliced ciabatta</strong> to the tray with a generous drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Tip: Cooking for 3 or more? Use 2 trays!</p><p>Return the tray[s] to the oven for 8-10 min or until golden</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/crab-aguachile-style-toasts-with-quick-pickled-chilli-potatoes/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once everything is ready, top the<strong> toasted</strong> <strong>ciabatta</strong> with the <strong>crab aguachile </strong>\u2013 these are your<strong> crab aguachile-style toasts</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/crab-aguachile-style-toasts-with-quick-pickled-chilli-potatoes/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>crab aguachile-style toasts </strong>garnished with the<strong> reserved coriander leaves </strong>and a <strong>lime wedge</strong></p><p>Serve the<strong> roast potatoes </strong>to the side topped with the<strong> quick-pickled chilli </strong>(not a fan of spice? Just add a little!)</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
